\par I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791150\charrsid7682985 Could you tell me what your father did, what his job was, when you were a lad.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10387110 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791150\charrsid7682985 My father? He worked for Mr. Maidment - cowman.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5517773 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791150\charrsid7682985 And your mother, did she work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10387110 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791150\charrsid7682985 No. My mother died at 29.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5517773 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791150\charrsid7682985 How old were you then? Were you very young?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10387110 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791150\charrsid7682985 Oh, there was }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1261998\charrsid7682985 4}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid12791150\charrsid7682985  of us, and I was about 3. Then there were }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1261998\charrsid7682985 2}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791150\charrsid7682985  younger than me.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5517773 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791150\charrsid7682985 Brothers and sisters, were they?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10387110 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1261998\charrsid7682985 1}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791150\charrsid7682985  sister and }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid1261998\charrsid7682985 3}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791150\charrsid7682985  brothers. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1261998\charrsid7682985 2}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791150\charrsid7682985 
 brothers, like, and me.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5517773 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791150\charrsid7682985 And when your mother died who looked after you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10387110 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791150\charrsid7682985 Grandmother.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5517773 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791150\charrsid7682985 Did you go and live with her?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10387110 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791150\charrsid7682985 They were going to put us in the workhouse, only there was a lady lived at the M}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid1261998\charrsid7682985 a}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791150\charrsid7682985 
nor, Mrs. Berry and she said - come up and see my grandmother, and she said if she'd look after us, she'd keep us in clothes and food. So she did, So my grandmother brought us up.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5517773 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791150\charrsid7682985 And was your grandfather alive, too?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10387110 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791150\charrsid7682985 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5517773 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791150\charrsid7682985 And so you all lived together, did you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10387110 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791150\charrsid7682985 Yes, yes. Number 18.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5517773 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791150\charrsid7682985 And was it your father's mother or your mother's mother, your grandmother who brought you up?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10387110 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791150\charrsid7682985 My father's mother, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5517773 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791150\charrsid7682985 Was she strict with you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10387110 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791150\charrsid7682985 No, very nice. So was my father. He never hit us, but he just spoke to us and we knew that was it. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5517773 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791150\charrsid7682985 And was he fussy about the way you behaved at table at mealtimes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10387110 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791150\charrsid7682985 Oh, we had to behave ourselves, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5517773 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791150\charrsid7682985 What rules did he have, can you remember?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10387110 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791150\charrsid7682985 We always had to say Grace.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5517773 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791150\charrsid7682985 All of you, or just one ..?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10387110 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791150\charrsid7682985 No, Dad'd say Grace and we just say Amen.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5517773 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791150\charrsid7682985 Can you remember the Grace he said?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10387110 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791150\charrsid7682985 Oh, something about - thank God for our good meals and that, and 'what we a}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid1261998\charrsid7682985 r}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791150\charrsid7682985 e about to receive may the Lord bless us'.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5517773 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791150\charrsid7682985 And then you'd sit down and ...?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10387110 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791150\charrsid7682985 ... have our meal.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5517773 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791150\charrsid7682985 Did you all sit together round the table?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10387110 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791150\charrsid7682985 Yes, Grampa and all. Grampa, he worked up in the Streets }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15943267\charrsid7682985 40}{\rtlch\fcs1 
\af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791150\charrsid7682985  years on}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3353460\charrsid7682985  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1261998\charrsid7682985 the }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791150\charrsid7682985 
farm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5517773 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791150\charrsid7682985 Was he a cowman, too?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10387110 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791150\charrsid7682985 Well, he was on the farm, do anything. But I didn't like my grandfather. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1261998\charrsid7682985 D
}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791150\charrsid7682985 idn't like me. He liked my brother and sister.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5517773 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791150\charrsid7682985 But not you. Why do you think that was?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10387110 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791150\charrsid7682985 I don't know. He didn't seem to like me at all.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5517773 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791150\charrsid7682985 And how did he show this dislike?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10387110 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791150\charrsid7682985 Well, he never used to talk to me, nor nothing much. But when I went away }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1261998\charrsid7682985 
to t}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791150\charrsid7682985 he Army and he were ill, he said he hoped I'd forgive him for all what he'd done to me. I said, well, there was nothing to forgive.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5517773 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791150\charrsid7682985 And were you the eldest of the brothers and sisters?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10387110 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791150\charrsid7682985 I was, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5517773 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791150\charrsid7682985 Can you just tell me again what their ages were? There was you, and then who was the next born?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10387110 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791150\charrsid7682985 Elsie was the oldest, and then there was me and then there was my brother who was 11 months younger than me.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5517773 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791150\charrsid7682985 How old was Elsie compared with you? How much older?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10387110 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791150\charrsid7682985 Oh, Elsie was about a year and }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1261998\charrsid7682985 3}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid12791150\charrsid7682985  months, older'n me. And then there was the baby. He was about a year and }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1261998\charrsid7682985 4}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791150\charrsid7682985  months younger.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5517773 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791150\charrsid7682985 And what was his name?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10387110 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791150\charrsid7682985 Albert, and my brother was named Fred
. I was named Percy ... and Elsie. We lived well. In them days, you see, my grandmother used to put a pot on and put the potatoes in the net, and the cabbage, all in ... boil in ... cool it all together.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5517773 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791150\charrsid7682985 What sort of net was it? String?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10387110 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791150\charrsid7682985 Yes, st
ring net, the old string net. And then we had a great piece of boil bacon, 'cos we always had a pig and then we'd' a killed that and hung that in the house, and then put racks upon there and dry it and then we'd live on that
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5517773 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791150\charrsid7682985 You had mostly bacon, then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10387110 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791150\charrsid7682985 Hm. We lived well, good plain food. And we never had pancakes, only once year, then we had a great pile.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5517773 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791150\charrsid7682985 Was that Shrove Tuesday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10387110 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791150\charrsid7682985 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5517773 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791150\charrsid7682985 And what about breakfast in the morning, did you have breakfast in those days?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10387110 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791150\charrsid7682985 Oh, yes, we had breakfast.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5517773 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791150\charrsid7682985 What did you eat for breakfast?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10387110 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791150\charrsid7682985 We had bread with dripping and sugar on it, things like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5517773 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791150\charrsid7682985 And your bread, did you make it yourselves, or did you buy it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10387110 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791150\charrsid7682985 Oh, well, we bought the bread.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5517773 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791150\charrsid7682985 Where did you buy it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10387110 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791150\charrsid7682985 Hepworth's Farm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5517773 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791150\charrsid7682985 They sold things there, then, too? And what was it like, the bread, was it brown or white?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10387110 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791150\charrsid7682985 White. Then when I left school, you see, I went there baking and then we used to bake with an old-fashioned wood oven. And then we used
 to make all our bread and then I used to go all round the village and that in a pony and cart, selling.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5517773 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791150\charrsid7682985 That was your first job?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10387110 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791150\charrsid7682985 Yes, and that was for 24 years.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5517773 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791150\charrsid7682985 How old were you when you started working?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10387110 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791150\charrsid7682985 14.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5517773 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791150\charrsid7682985 Can you remember what you first got paid?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10387110 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791150\charrsid7682985 Never had much, about }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1261998\charrsid7682985 10}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid12791150\charrsid7682985  shillings, if I had that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5517773 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791150\charrsid7682985 And what hours did you work?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10387110 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791150\charrsid7682985 Hours? All the time.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5517773 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791150\charrsid7682985 You never had no set hours. No Saturdays?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10387110 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791150\charrsid7682985 I used to have to bake Saturdays, you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5517773 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791150\charrsid7682985 And Sundays, what did you do Sundays?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10387110 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791150\charrsid7682985 Sundays I had to go and make the sponge for the bread for Mondays, and that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5517773 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791150\charrsid7682985 So you never had a day off?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10387110 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791150\charrsid7682985 Well, if I did have a day off I used to have to pay somebody }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1261998\charrsid7682985 to }{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791150\charrsid7682985 do my work.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5517773 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791150\charrsid7682985 And what time did you get up in the morning?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10387110 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791150\charrsid7682985 About }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6770402\charrsid7682985 {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname time}
{\xmlattr\xmlattrns0{\xmlattrname Minute}{\xmlattrvalue 0}}{\xmlattr\xmlattrns0{\xmlattrname Hour}{\xmlattrvalue 18}}}6}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791150\charrsid7682985  o'clock{\*\xmlclose}.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5517773 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791150\charrsid7682985 Can you describe a day to me, say, your first day at work? Can you remember your first day?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10387110 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791150\charrsid7682985 Started up in the morning {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname time}{\xmlattr\xmlattrns0{\xmlattrname Minute}{\xmlattrvalue 0}}
{\xmlattr\xmlattrns0{\xmlattrname Hour}{\xmlattrvalue 18}}}6 o'clock{\*\xmlclose} with the bread, yes, and then go home had me breakfast - that be only just across the road.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5517773 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791150\charrsid7682985 What time would that be, the breakfast?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10387110 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791150\charrsid7682985 Oh, about {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname time}{\xmlattr\xmlattrns0{\xmlattrname Minute}{\xmlattrvalue 0}}
{\xmlattr\xmlattrns0{\xmlattrname Hour}{\xmlattrvalue 8}}}8 o'clock{\*\xmlclose}. And then I'd go back again, get the horse ready, and that, and go round with the bread. Sometimes I didn't finish 'till {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname time}
{\xmlattr\xmlattrns0{\xmlattrname Minute}{\xmlattrvalue 0}}{\xmlattr\xmlattrns0{\xmlattrname Hour}{\xmlattrvalue 18}}}6 o'clock{\*\xmlclose} at }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6770402\charrsid7682985 n}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid12791150\charrsid7682985 ight.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5517773 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791150\charrsid7682985 Did you get a break at lunchtime?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10387110 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791150\charrsid7682985 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5517773 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791150\charrsid7682985 No break {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname time}{\xmlattr\xmlattrns0{\xmlattrname Minute}{\xmlattrvalue 0}}{\xmlattr\xmlattrns0{\xmlattrname 
Hour}{\xmlattrvalue 12}}}midday{\*\xmlclose}?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10387110 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791150\charrsid7682985 No. I had me dinner.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5517773 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791150\charrsid7682985 Did you come home for that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10387110 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791150\charrsid7682985 No, sometimes I had me dinner over there with them.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5517773 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791150\charrsid7682985 Did they feed you well?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10387110 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791150\charrsid7682985 Oh, yes, they did.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5517773 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791150\charrsid7682985 Was that bacon, too?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10387110 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791150\charrsid7682985 Oh, we had bacon. And I tell you what we used to have a lot on, big bread puddings baked in their oven.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5517773 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791150\charrsid7682985 Did they have currants in then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10387110 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791150\charrsid7682985 Yes, currants and raisins. And Christmas time we used to light the oven special and cook all the people's cakes and turkeys and fowls.

\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5517773 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791150\charrsid7682985 People used to bring them round?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10387110 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791150\charrsid7682985 Bring them round to the bakehouse. We used to cook them for nothing for the Light the oven special.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5517773 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791150\charrsid7682985 How long did that go on for, that custom of baking for the village?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10387110 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791150\charrsid7682985 I was there 24 y
ears, then Mr. Hales retired from the Swan and took a little farm up near, and of course, I went with him, and then the old oven fell down then. And then Strongs at }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6770402\charrsid7682985 Woodborough}{\rtlch\fcs1 
\af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791150\charrsid7682985  took over.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5517773 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791150\charrsid7682985 And then they stopped baking for people when they took over?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10387110 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791150\charrsid7682985 Yes, he took it and come round.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5517773 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791150\charrsid7682985 Your grandmother when she cooked for you, did she cook on an open fire?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10387110 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791150\charrsid7682985 Yes, a great old fire and a big oven at the side. And in them days we all had ... Grandmother had white quilt on the bed, white curtains,
 everything was white. No colours.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5517773 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791150\charrsid7682985 Why was that, did she disapprove of colours?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10387110 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791150\charrsid7682985 No, I don't know, I be all ...
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5517773 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791150\charrsid7682985 Did everyone have white in the homes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10387110 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791150\charrsid7682985 Yes, all their beds. We had in our place.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5517773 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791150\charrsid7682985 Did it mean a lot of washing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10387110 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791150\charrsid7682985 Oh, Mother do washing, great big tub on a stool. She always washing }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6770402\charrsid7682985 on }{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791150\charrsid7682985 Monday.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5517773 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791150\charrsid7682985 And what sort of soap did she use?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10387110 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791150\charrsid7682985 Sunlight.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5517773 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791150\charrsid7682985 And a washing board, or mangle?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10387110 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791150\charrsid7682985 She had one of them old boards you rub the things up and down on. No mangle.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5517773 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791150\charrsid7682985 That came later, did it, the mangle? How long did her wash take her on Monday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10387110 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791150\charrsid7682985 Nearly all day, 'cos after she'd washed she had to clean all up.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5517773 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791150\charrsid7682985 Where did she wash, in the kitchen?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10387110 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791150\charrsid7682985 Yes. And then there was getting it dry, you see. And then, it took her a}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6770402\charrsid7682985 ll
}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791150\charrsid7682985  the time then ironing.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5517773 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791150\charrsid7682985 Would she iron the same day?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10387110 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791150\charrsid7682985 No. She'd damp it all down and roll it all up, put it in the basket and then she'd iron it the next day.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5517773 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791150\charrsid7682985 And what kind of irons did she have?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10387110 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791150\charrsid7682985 Them old-fashioned little irons, we used to put them by the fire and heat them. Not electric like we got.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5517773 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791150\charrsid7682985 Did she do it all on her own?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10387110 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791150\charrsid7682985 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5517773 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791150\charrsid7682985 Did she get any help from neighbours or anybody in her housework?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10387110 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791150\charrsid7682985 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5517773 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791150\charrsid7682985 Did everything herself?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10387110 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791150\charrsid7682985 Yes. And then we had an iron sheet to put on there to do her toast on.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5517773 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791150\charrsid7682985 A sort of grid was it? And a kettle?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10387110 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791150\charrsid7682985 Yes. Used to hang it on the grate. Yes, old kettle, like these.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5517773 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791150\charrsid7682985 Did she drink tea much?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10387110 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791150\charrsid7682985 Oh, yes, we had tea
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5517773 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791150\charrsid7682985 Tea and coffee, or just tea?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10387110 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791150\charrsid7682985 Tea. {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname City}}Cocoa{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose}, we had.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5517773 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791150\charrsid7682985 When was that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10387110 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791150\charrsid7682985 
We used to have that sometimes nights, going to bed. If we disobeyed, Dad said we never had to have no tea and so we didn't have any, but while he was gone out Grandmother used to come upstairs and bring us some. So we did we had our teas.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5517773 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791150\charrsid7682985 What would you normally have for tea of an evening?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10387110 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791150\charrsid7682985 Might have bread and butter, or bread and dripping, or we might have egg, not very often.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5517773 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791150\charrsid7682985 How often?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10387110 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791150\charrsid7682985 Perhaps we'd have them twice a week.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5517773 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791150\charrsid7682985 And in the Autumn, too, and the Winter, when eggs are scarcer?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10387110 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791150\charrsid7682985 Didn't have much - many eggs then.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5517773 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791150\charrsid7682985 How did she cook the eggs for you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10387110 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791150\charrsid7682985 In a little saucepan, boiled them. Sometimes fried them. But we had a lot of dripping. Saved our own dripping.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5517773 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791150\charrsid7682985 And jam, did you have jam?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10387110 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791150\charrsid7682985 Make our own. Grandmother made her own jam.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5517773 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791150\charrsid7682985 Did she ever buy it, or was it all homema}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6770402\charrsid7682985 d}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid12791150\charrsid7682985 e?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10387110 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791150\charrsid7682985 If she had enough we used to buy it off. And then she used to make dandelion wine. We'd go out and pick the 
dandelion heads. And rhubarb with and then the jars - sometimes we were sitting indoors, you could hear the corks blowing out of the jars.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5517773 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791150\charrsid7682985 Was it quite strong?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10387110 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791150\charrsid7682985 Yes! Was strong.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5517773 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791150\charrsid7682985 How did she learn to make it, do you think? Did her mother make it before her?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10387110 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791150\charrsid7682985 I should think so, 'cos she had a big pan in the pantry place and I'd get a of yeast, you see, and work it, and all.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5517773 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791150\charrsid7682985 And did she let the children drink the wine, or was it just for the grownups
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10387110 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791150\charrsid7682985 Oh, we didn't have it. No, we didn't have no wine.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5517773 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791150\charrsid7682985 When did they drink it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10387110 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791150\charrsid7682985 In the evening, sometimes. We had milk.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5517773 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791150\charrsid7682985 Where did the milk come from?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10387110 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791150\charrsid7682985 Mr. Maidment's farm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5517773 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791150\charrsid7682985 Did your father bring that back with him?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10387110 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791150\charrsid7682985 Yes. We had milk then. Grandfather used to go over the Swan sometimes }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6770402\charrsid7682985 to}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791150\charrsid7682985  have a pint.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5517773 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791150\charrsid7682985 How did you get on with your brothers and sisters, did you play together?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10387110 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791150\charrsid7682985 I loved me sister. My brother and me didn't get on very well.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5517773 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791150\charrsid7682985 Was that Albert, or the other one?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10387110 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791150\charrsid7682985 No, Fred, 'cos we didn't know Albert, you see. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5517773 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791150\charrsid7682985 Why didn't you know Albert?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10387110 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791150\charrsid7682985 Well, he was a lot younger, and then he died. He died at a year and - we he only lived a year and }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid6770402\charrsid7682985 3}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791150\charrsid7682985  months, after Mother.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5517773 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791150\charrsid7682985 And Fred and you used to quarrel, did you?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10387110 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791150\charrsid7682985 Well, we did.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5517773 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791150\charrsid7682985 Why do you think you did? Was there rivalry?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10387110 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791150\charrsid7682985 
I suppose we didn't get on - and what we used to often do ... there was an old lady lived in Maniford Road and we used to go down there for a penn'orth of bread pudding, take our hoops down - go d
own there and get a penn'orth of bread pudding, and we used to eat that coming back. And what we three had to do - Elsie had to help Grandmother, Fred had to get in the coal and I had to clean the boots and knives, and all. We had that to do every week 'f
ore we could go out to play.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5517773 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791150\charrsid7682985 First thing in the morning you had to do that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10387110 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791150\charrsid7682985 Hm, we had to do that every Saturday.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5517773 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791150\charrsid7682985 Did it take a long time to clean the boots?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10387110 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791150\charrsid7682985 Yes. And all the knives on the knife board.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5517773 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791150\charrsid7682985 Anything else you had to do? Anything in the garden, or look after the pig.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10387110 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791150\charrsid7682985 Well, we had to weed, and that. Oh, yes, we had to weed and look after the pig sometimes, and feed him. We always had a pig.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5517773 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791150\charrsid7682985 Any fowls?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10387110 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791150\charrsid7682985 Ah, we used to have fowls.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5517773 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791150\charrsid7682985 Did you have to clean them out?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10387110 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791150\charrsid7682985 Yes, clean them about every week, and put them in fresh nest boxes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5517773 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791150\charrsid7682985 And anything else with the fowls?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10387110 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791150\charrsid7682985 No, not with the fowls. Oh, we used to sit them and get some chickens.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5517773 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791150\charrsid7682985 And did you get any pocket money?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10387110 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791150\charrsid7682985 What was it we used to have? About threepence a week.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5517773 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791150\charrsid7682985 What did you spend it on?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10387110 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791150\charrsid7682985 Sweets.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5517773 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791150\charrsid7682985 You'd buy those at the Swann?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10387110 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791150\charrsid7682985 Yes, you'd get any amount for a penny, or a halfpenny ... halfpennyworth of liquorice.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5517773 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791150\charrsid7682985 What else did you get besides liquorice, was there anything else you could buy in the way of sweets?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10387110 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791150\charrsid7682985 Oh, any sweets.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5517773 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791150\charrsid7682985 A lot of varieties, were }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6770402\charrsid7682985 there}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid12791150\charrsid7682985 ?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10387110 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791150\charrsid7682985 Oh, yes, Jube-jubes and things like that, we used to have.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5517773 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791150\charrsid7682985 Did you ever spend the money on anything else?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10387110 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791150\charrsid7682985 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5517773 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791150\charrsid7682985 Did you give any presents to your grandmother, or your father, or your brother and sisters at birthdays and Christmas, can you remember?

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10387110 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791150\charrsid7682985 We never had nothing to give, no, not like we have today.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5517773 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791150\charrsid7682985 But you ate well?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10387110 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791150\charrsid7682985 Yes, we did have ... always good food, old}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6770402\charrsid7682985  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid12791150\charrsid7682985 fashioned food.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5517773 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791150\charrsid7682985 But you weren't hungry ever?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10387110 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791150\charrsid7682985 No! Potatoes and turnips and }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6770402\charrsid7682985 s}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid12791150\charrsid7682985 wedes, all what Grandpa grew in the garden.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5517773 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791150\charrsid7682985 And would you have your main meal at midday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10387110 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791150\charrsid7682985 Yes, always dinnertime, Grandpa'd come home, and all.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5517773 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791150\charrsid7682985 What time would that be, about 1 o'clock?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10387110 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6770402\charrsid7682985 12}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791150\charrsid7682985  o'clock.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5517773 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791150\charrsid7682985 And then tea at ...?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10387110 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791150\charrsid7682985 Tea at }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6770402\charrsid7682985 5}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791150\charrsid7682985 
 - well, we used to have our tea afore Grandpa'd come home, }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6770402\charrsid7682985 4}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791150\charrsid7682985  o'clock, when we come out of school.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5517773 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791150\charrsid7682985 Tell me about the school, was it in }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15943267\charrsid7682985 Wilcot}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid12791150\charrsid7682985 ?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10387110 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791150\charrsid7682985 Yes, just up here.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5517773 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791150\charrsid7682985 How old were you when you started?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10387110 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791150\charrsid7682985 
I went to school very early ... I haven't got the photos now ... I went to school when I were three. I went in petticoats (laughter) and they - we had our photos took at the school once 
and they took my pinafore off 'cos it had a hole in it. I have the photos somewhere, I don't know where.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5517773 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791150\charrsid7682985 Why did you wear petticoats? Did boys only go into trousers when they were older?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10387110 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791150\charrsid7682985 I suppose that was it. I went to school in petticoats, little dress and petticoats.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5517773 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791150\charrsid7682985 Did a lot of children go as young as }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12322035\charrsid7682985 3}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid12791150\charrsid7682985  in those days?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10387110 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791150\charrsid7682985 Yes. And then my brother, Fred, he went in a little velvet suit and white collar round.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5517773 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791150\charrsid7682985 And when you went at }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12322035\charrsid7682985 3}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid12791150\charrsid7682985 , how long did you stay at the school? All day, or was it just the morning?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10387110 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791150\charrsid7682985 Oh, stayed all day.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5517773 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791150\charrsid7682985 And come home for dinner?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10387110 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791150\charrsid7682985 Yes, and then go back and then come home for tea.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5517773 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791150\charrsid7682985 And what did you do, do you remember? When you were very little, at the school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10387110 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791150\charrsid7682985 Do some }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15943267\charrsid7682985 scribbling}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid12791150\charrsid7682985 , sit up}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12322035\charrsid7682985  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15943267\charrsid7682985 scri}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791150\charrsid7682985 
bbling at the desk, scribbling on books.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5517773 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791150\charrsid7682985 Did they teach you anything, or was that later on?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10387110 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791150\charrsid7682985 That was later on, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5517773 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791150\charrsid7682985 What about singing, did you do any singing when you first went?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10387110 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791150\charrsid7682985 We done a bit of singing.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5517773 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791150\charrsid7682985 Anything else you can remember?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10387110 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791150\charrsid7682985 I was fond of singing, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5517773 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791150\charrsid7682985 What did you like to sing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10387110 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791150\charrsid7682985 All sorts of hymns, and 'Lightly Rowed' and all them kind of things.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5517773 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791150\charrsid7682985 'Lightly Rowed'? How does that go?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10387110 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791150\charrsid7682985 'Lightly Row, Lightly row ...', and then we used to ha
ve 'I love my little cat, I do; his coat is Oh so warm, comes with me each day to school and sit upon the form'.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5517773 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791150\charrsid7682985 You learnt that there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10387110 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791150\charrsid7682985 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5517773 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791150\charrsid7682985 And any other rhymes you remember?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10387110 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791150\charrsid7682985 Well, we done all the, kind of nursery rhymes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5517773 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791150\charrsid7682985 How many of you were there in the school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10387110 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791150\charrsid7682985 We had a master and a mistress, I suppose there were about 40 of us.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5517773 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791150\charrsid7682985 Was it all one room?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10387110 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791150\charrsid7682985 No, there was the classroom, a little room, and then the big room.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5517773 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791150\charrsid7682985 And when you first went did you go in the big room?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10387110 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791150\charrsid7682985 No, little one.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5517773 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791150\charrsid7682985 In the little one with the little ones?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10387110 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791150\charrsid7682985 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5517773 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791150\charrsid7682985 And who taught you then in the little class?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10387110 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791150\charrsid7682985 She was a Mrs. Wellman then.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5517773 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791150\charrsid7682985 And was she a good teacher?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10387110 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791150\charrsid7682985 Oh, yes, very good, she was. Kind.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5517773 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791150\charrsid7682985 Did she ever punish you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10387110 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791150\charrsid7682985 Sometimes we had to stand in the corner.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5517773 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791150\charrsid7682985 That was the punishment?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10387110 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791150\charrsid7682985 Yes, with our hands on our heads.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5517773 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791150\charrsid7682985 Did she let you talk?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10387110 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791150\charrsid7682985 No, had to be quiet. Very good she was. She was kind, but we had to do what we were told.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5517773 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791150\charrsid7682985 When you were at home could you talk at meals? Were you allowed to talk?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10387110 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791150\charrsid7682985 No, we didn't say nothing, only please could we have something.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5517773 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791150\charrsid7682985 Were your grandparents and your father strict about manners?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10387110 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791150\charrsid7682985 Oh, they were. We were brought up well. Yes. And we had to say 'please' and 'thank you' wherever we went.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5517773 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791150\charrsid7682985 And did you have to eat everything on your plate?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10387110 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791150\charrsid7682985 Yes, if we left anything we used to get it. (laughter) But sometimes we didn't like it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5517773 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791150\charrsid7682985 No, and then, what?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10387110 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791150\charrsid7682985 We didn't have it! (laughter)
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5517773 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791150\charrsid7682985 If there was something your grandmother cooked that you didn't like, did she say you had to eat something of it, or not?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10387110 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791150\charrsid7682985 No, she never used to force us, no. she was good like that. She used to give us something else, because she was a good Grann}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12322035\charrsid7682985 y}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791150\charrsid7682985 . She lived 'till she were 80.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5517773 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791150\charrsid7682985 You called her 'Grann}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12322035\charrsid7682985 y}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid12791150\charrsid7682985 ', did you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10387110 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791150\charrsid7682985 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5517773 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791150\charrsid7682985 And your Grandfather?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10387110 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791150\charrsid7682985 Grandpa. Always go to Church, Grann}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12322035\charrsid7682985 y}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid12791150\charrsid7682985  did.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5517773 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791150\charrsid7682985 And all of you go to Church?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10387110 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791150\charrsid7682985 Yes. Went to Sunday School.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5517773 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791150\charrsid7682985 When was that, the afternoon?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10387110 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791150\charrsid7682985 Yes, afternoon Sunday School. Sometimes we used to go mornings.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5517773 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791150\charrsid7682985 Did you wear special clothes on a Sunday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10387110 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791150\charrsid7682985 Well, we had Sunday clothes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5517773 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791150\charrsid7682985 Did everybody have that in those days?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10387110 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791150\charrsid7682985 Yes. Grandmother used to wear a cape and bonnet.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5517773 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791150\charrsid7682985 And what did you wear.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10387110 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791150\charrsid7682985 Just a little suit.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5517773 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791150\charrsid7682985 And a hat or cap?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10387110 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791150\charrsid7682985 Oh, a cap; and a white collar.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5517773 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791150\charrsid7682985 And a tie?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10387110 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791150\charrsid7682985 Kind of a bow, then. I loved going to Church and Sunday School. 'Cos when I got olde
r and grown up I used to teach at Sunday School down here. Always had nearly }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12322035\charrsid7682985 60}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791150\charrsid7682985  children.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5517773 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791150\charrsid7682985 You had 60 to teach?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10387110 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791150\charrsid7682985 Hm, and I had some helpers, but I was the superintendent of the school.
