\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10387110 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791150\charrsid7682985 Yes, I wanted to go, 'cos I used to go over there when I was a boy, }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7542356\charrsid7682985 
messing}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791150\charrsid7682985  about.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5517773 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791150\charrsid7682985 I see, so he knew you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10387110 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791150\charrsid7682985 Hm, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5517773 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791150\charrsid7682985 What sort of messing about?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10387110 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791150\charrsid7682985 You know, go over there and sometimes I'd clean out the stable whe
re the horse was, do little jobs like that. And then go in the bakery and watch them.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5517773 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791150\charrsid7682985 Would he pay you for the jobs?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10387110 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791150\charrsid7682985 Oh, no, only used to go over there.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5517773 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791150\charrsid7682985 Just for something to do, was it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10387110 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791150\charrsid7682985 Hm, Mrs. Hales used to give me a lump of cake sometimes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5517773 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791150\charrsid7682985 And then he came over and asked if you could start there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10387110 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791150\charrsid7682985 Yes, and I were there 34 years. I had a letter from his daughter Christmas}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7542356\charrsid7682985 
, }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791150\charrsid7682985 he's married, lives down Sherborne, got a farm. She sent me }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5517773 \'a3}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791150\charrsid7682985 
1 for Christmas.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5517773 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791150\charrsid7682985 What did you light your house with in those days, lamps?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10387110 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791150\charrsid7682985 
Oh, lamps, oil lamps. We had oil lamps in the Church. I used to go down there every Friday and it used to take me two hours take all them lamps down and fill 'em with oil and put 'em back up again.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5517773 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791150\charrsid7682985 Did you have to clean them, then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10387110 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791150\charrsid7682985 
Yes, and I used to go down there Fridays, I used to take old Peter with me then, 'cos I didn't like going through the churchyard at night, and I used go down there and light the stove - they had a fire - right down under-gro
und, big fire, that did warm the church with hot water pipes all the way round. I used to say to old Peter, 'you stop up there 'till I come up'. I used to go down Friday nights, Saturday nights, and then Sunday mornings and hook it up and - beautiful and 
warm, the Church, then. Now 'tis heated with oil. I used to go down once a week, every Friday, and draw up the clock.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5517773 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791150\charrsid7682985 How did you do that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10387110 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791150\charrsid7682985 Great big weights, one's a hundredweight and one's half. You had to draw them right from the bottom up to the top of the tower.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5517773 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791150\charrsid7682985 Do they still do that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10387110 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791150\charrsid7682985 Yes, they do that now, once a week.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5517773 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791150\charrsid7682985 What about bell ringing, did you do anything like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10387110 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791150\charrsid7682985 They only had the one bell. Used to ring that, that's all. It don't see 76 year ago I were born at Wilcot.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5517773 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791150\charrsid7682985 
Did your father leave your clothes and that kind of thing to your grandmother or did he do anything like that himself? Choosing your boots, or anything like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10387110 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791150\charrsid7682985 Grandmother used to buy all our clothes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5517773 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791150\charrsid7682985 And the boots, too?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10387110 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791150\charrsid7682985 
Yes, she used to buy all our boots. And when we were on holidays we had to take all our clothes off and have old clothes on to play about in.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5517773 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791150\charrsid7682985 Did you have special clothes for school, or just your ordinary clothes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10387110 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791150\charrsid7682985 No, we had a better Sunday set of clothes, to go to Church Sundays.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5517773 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791150\charrsid7682985 And then would you keep them on the whole day Sunday, or take them off when you got back from Church?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10387110 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791150\charrsid7682985 No, keep them on all day Sunday.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5517773 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791150\charrsid7682985 Where did she store them away then, for the rest of the week?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10387110 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791150\charrsid7682985 Upstairs in a box. Grandmother was very particular about our clothes. We never had no holes in them, she was always darning them.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5517773 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791150\charrsid7682985 Did she teach you anything in the home? Or was it mostly you sister who had to do things in the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10387110 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791150\charrsid7682985 No, she used to make us all be tidy. If we put anything about ... if we}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5117083\charrsid7682985 
 had}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791150\charrsid7682985  some books or papers, we all had to put them back before going to bed. Put 'em up tidy.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5517773 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791150\charrsid7682985 Did you have homework to do from school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10387110 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791150\charrsid7682985 No, didn't do no homework. Grandmother was very particular in making us }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5117083\charrsid7682985 
a bit}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791150\charrsid7682985  tidy.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5517773 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791150\charrsid7682985 Did you have to make your own beds?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10387110 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791150\charrsid7682985 No!
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5517773 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791150\charrsid7682985 She made the beds for you always?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10387110 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791150\charrsid7682985 Yes. Grandmother never - we didn't have to do nothing like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5517773 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791150\charrsid7682985 No, housework at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10387110 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791150\charrsid7682985 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5517773 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791150\charrsid7682985 Not even your sister? She made your sister's bed, did she?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10387110 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791150\charrsid7682985 No, Elsie had to do ...
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5517773 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791150\charrsid7682985 Elsie did the bed. And your father and grandfather, did they do work in }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5117083\charrsid7682985 the}
{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791150\charrsid7682985  house at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10387110 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791150\charrsid7682985 No, they seemed to do only the garden, and that. 'Course, Dad couldn't do lot with }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid5117083\charrsid7682985 1}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791150\charrsid7682985  arm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5517773 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791150\charrsid7682985 Do you remember that happening to your father?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10387110 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791150\charrsid7682985 Oh, yes, got a photo of him now, with }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5117083\charrsid7682985 1}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid12791150\charrsid7682985  arm. That's why he grew a beard
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5517773 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791150\charrsid7682985 Were most people clean shaven then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10387110 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791150\charrsid7682985 Hm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10387110 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791150\charrsid7682985 He worked for the Church, see, for years and years. I worked for 
the Church 45 years, for nothing. Never had nothing for it, I didn't want it. Done for the love of the thing.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5517773 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791150\charrsid7682985 What work did you do? You were saying you did the lamps and the clock.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10387110 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791150\charrsid7682985 I used to clean all the brasses, lect}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5117083\charrsid7682985 e}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid12791150\charrsid7682985 rn, all on the Altar. And Grandmother and Aunt Mary - that was her sister - they used to go down every Thursday and clean the Church right through, do all the mats and all. They used to get about ... did they get }{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5517773 \'a3}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791150\charrsid7682985 3 a year? No, I don't expect they did. They used to go every week. A
nd then twice a year they did spring clean the Church right through. Well, Dad, when he used to dig the graves and do}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5117083\charrsid7682985  all that, he only used to get 13}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid12791150\charrsid7682985  shillings.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5517773 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791150\charrsid7682985 He did all the grave digging, did he?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10387110 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791150\charrsid7682985 Yes, with }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5117083\charrsid7682985 1}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid12791150\charrsid7682985  arm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5517773 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5117083\charrsid7682985 13}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791150\charrsid7682985  shillings a year?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10387110 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791150\charrsid7682985 Yes. No, }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5117083\charrsid7682985 13}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid12791150\charrsid7682985  shillings every one what were buried.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10387110 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791150\charrsid7682985 Oh, I was going to say, 13/- a year! A lot of work and with }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5117083\charrsid7682985 1}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791150\charrsid7682985  arm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10387110 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791150\charrsid7682985 Yes, 'cos, I mean, }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5117083\charrsid7682985 6}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid12791150\charrsid7682985  foot a grave is. Now, I mean, they get }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5117083\charrsid7682985 3}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791150\charrsid7682985  or }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid5117083\charrsid7682985 4}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791150\charrsid7682985  pound.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5517773 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791150\charrsid7682985 Were there a lot of funerals in those days, do you think, more than there are today?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10387110 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791150\charrsid7682985 A good few.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5517773 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791150\charrsid7682985 Did people make more of an occasion of it? Did they have a supper after a funeral?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10387110 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791150\charrsid7682985 No, all Grandmother used to do, and all, always used to have black crepe all round her cake and all round her bonnet.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5517773 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791150\charrsid7682985 If a relative died do you mean?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10387110 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791150\charrsid7682985 Yes. Nothing coloured or white put on 'till after }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5117083\charrsid7682985 6}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791150\charrsid7682985  months.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5517773 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791150\charrsid7682985 And then after }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5117083\charrsid7682985 6 }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid12791150\charrsid7682985 months?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10387110 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791150\charrsid7682985 Yes, then they did put on some grey or anything like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5517773 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791150\charrsid7682985 When did they go back to ordinary colours?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10387110 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791150\charrsid7682985 A year.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5517773 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791150\charrsid7682985 After your mother died, do you think you children were put in black?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10387110 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791150\charrsid7682985 No, I don't think we were, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5517773 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791150\charrsid7682985 It was for grownups, was it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10387110 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791150\charrsid7682985 Yes. \{BLANK\} Well, I think May's was }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5117083\charrsid7682985 50 }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid12791150\charrsid7682985 odd pounds. That was cremation at {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname City}}Salisbury{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose}. A lot of money isn't it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5517773 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791150\charrsid7682985 Did you get it from the insurance?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10387110 PH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791150\charrsid7682985 We had a - May was took to {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname PlaceName}}Wilcot{\*\xmlclose} 
{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname PlaceType}}Church{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose} for one night and then we went there next day and had a service, then we went straight on to {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname City}}Salisbury
